    </ol>
    <ol>
        <li><span style="color:#087b08"><strong>Autocannons</strong></span> : These usually range from 20mm to 35mm, in general there's two ammo types HE and APDS, HE is used to effectively combat larger groups of infantry and lightly armored vehicles such as trucks and technicals, while APDS is used against other IFVs, heavily armored APCs,  or even to a very limited extend MBTs when hitting from the sides and back, in general Autocannon ammo should be strongly conserved as it is the main weaponry of an IFV and has limited ammo reserve, which is especially true for the APDS as these have a very limited supply and should be used with care more so than the HE, as always Targets should be Flanked for maximum effect.</li>
    </ol>
